BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:5xShIqe3oOdR6-rZmQV6k
SUMMARY:History Café: Indigenous Forestry
DTSTAMP:20260214T003622Z
DTSTART:20260218T183000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join local Tribal forestry professionals\\\, who will trace mil
	lennia of stewardship by Indigenous peoples to manage forests based on hol
	istic worldviews of connectedness of communities with their environments. 
	With colonization\\\, this ethos was displaced with forest policy centered
	 on timber production\\\, resulting in disruption of environmental process
	es. Today\\\, Indigenous peoples are asserting greater influence over mana
	gement of their ancestral forest lands through their exercise of self-dete
	rmination and application of traditional knowledge and western science. \\
	nHistory Café is produced as a partnership between HistoryLink and MOHAI. 
	\\nASL Interpretation and CART captioning are available during the program
	. In addition\\\, a limited number of Assistive Listening Devices are avai
	lable upon request. For more accessibility support\\\, email programs@moha
	i.org two weeks before the program. \\nGrab some food for thought–light fo
	od and drink will be available to purchase in the atrium. \\nIf you can’t 
	make it to the museum\\\, tune in live on the MOHAI YouTube channel to vir
	tually attend this event.\n\nFrom MOHAI - Museum of History & Industry
URL:https://mohai.org/event/history-cafe-indigenous-forestry/
LOCATION:Faye G. Allen Grand Atrium\\\, MOHAI 860 Terry Ave N\\\, Seattle\\
	\, WA\\\, 98109\\\, United States
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:o_A5WnV9Be9xKJD2-jDry
SUMMARY:DAY OF REMEMBRANCE 2026 - TOURS &amp\; RESOURCES
DTSTAMP:20260214T003622Z
DTSTART:20260221T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:The Day of Remembrance\, observed on February 19\, marks the an
	niversary of the signing of EO 9066\, which set into motion the incarcerat
	ion of Japanese Americans and their families during WWII. You can learn mo
	re about this historic breach of civil rights through a number of events t
	hroughout February\, March and April.\n\nFrom Wing Luke Museum
URL:https://www.wingluke.org/eventscalendar/2026-day-of-remembrance-beyond-
	the-barbed-wire
LOCATION:Wing Luke Museum\, 719 South King Street\, Seattle\, WA\, 98104
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT169H30M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:EhlUOfwjdJp3E1qgvsUYp
SUMMARY:Sensory Friendly Morning
DTSTAMP:20260214T003622Z
DTSTART:20260228T090000Z
DESCRIPTION:This event welcomes adults and families who may benefit from a 
	low-sensory environment to explore the museum. During this event\\\, the m
	useum will be closed to the general public and the lights and sounds in th
	e gallery will be lowered. A sensory map and information about what to exp
	ect during your visit to MOHAI will be provided via email following regist
	ration. Spots are limited so register early! \\nTítulo: Horas más tranquil
	as\\nFecha/hora: sábado 28 de febrero\\\, de 9:00 a. m. a 11:00 a. m.\\nCo
	sto: gratuito con inscripción previa \\nEste evento da la bienvenida a adu
	ltos y familias que puedan beneficiarse de un entorno con bajo nivel senso
	rial para explorar el museo. Durante el evento\\\, el museo permanecerá ce
	rrado al público en general\\\, y se bajarán las luces y los sonidos de la
	 galería. Tras la inscripción\\\, se enviará por correo electrónico un map
	a sensorial e información sobre lo que puede esperar durante su visita al 
	Museum of History & Industry (MOHAI\\\, Museo de Historia e Industria). Lo
	s cupos son limitados\\\, así que inscríbase pronto.\n\nFrom MOHAI - Museu
	m of History & Industry
URL:https://mohai.org/event/sensory-friendly-morning/
LOCATION:MOHAI\\\, MOHAI - 860 Terry Ave N\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98109\\\,
	 United States
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
