UID:p5TMKlfp_QxGI5w3qGT5U
SUMMARY:Bicycle Repair Workshop with Bike Works
DTSTAMP:20260214T003622Z
DTSTART:20260305T173000Z
DESCRIPTION:This event has sold out\\nAspiring and experienced cyclists ali
	ke agree that life is better when your bike works. This is why representat
	ives from Bike Works will be onsite during Free First Thursday to teach tw
	o hour-long bicycle repair workshops. Learn the basics that will keep you 
	safely riding after the rubber meets the road. While you’re at the museum\
	\\, get a crash course in Seattle cycling history from MOHAI’s exhibit\\\,
	 Riding Together: 135 Years of Cycling in Seattle. \\nThese workshops are 
	offered for free and require registration\\\, as space is limited. For acc
	essibility support\\\, general inquiries\\\, or to be added to a wait list
	 please email programs@mohai.org.\n\nFrom MOHAI - Museum of History & Indu
	stry
URL:https://mohai.org/event/bicycle-repair-workshop-with-bike-works/2026-03
	-05/1/
LOCATION:Microsoft Lakefront Pavilion\\\, MOHAI - 860 Terry Ave N\\\, Seatt
	le\\\, WA\\\, 98109\\\, United States
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
