BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Mj23xZBqD6st8VI-5aYmc
SUMMARY:History Café: Seattle Mystic Al Hubbard
DTSTAMP:20260214T003622Z
DTSTART:20260318T183000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join Brad Holden\\\, author of Seattle Mystic Alfred M. Hubbard
	 for a discussion of one of Seattle’s most mysterious figures. Hubbard fir
	st appeared in the papers in 1919 for his supposed invention of a perpetua
	l motion machine that harnessed energy from Earth’s atmosphere. From there
	\\\, he transformed himself into a bootlegger\\\, radio pioneer\\\, top-se
	cret spy\\\, and eventually “the Johnny Appleseed of LSD”. \\nHistory Café
	 is produced as a partnership between HistoryLink and MOHAI. \\nASL Interp
	retation and CART captioning are available during the program. In addition
	\\\, a limited number of Assistive Listening Devices are available upon re
	quest. For more accessibility support\\\, email programs@mohai.org two wee
	ks before the program. \\nGrab some food for thought–light food and drink 
	will be available to purchase in the atrium. \\nIf you can’t make it to th
	e museum\\\, tune in live on the MOHAI YouTube channel to virtually attend
	 this event.\n\nFrom MOHAI - Museum of History & Industry
URL:https://mohai.org/event/history-cafe-seattle-mystic-al-hubbard/
LOCATION:Faye G. Allen Grand Atrium\\\, MOHAI 860 Terry Ave N\\\, Seattle\\
	\, WA\\\, 98109\\\, United States
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:rAhkV_gsbZ3_hqHv7g1v9
SUMMARY:Motorcycle Riding Experience with Motorcycle Safety Foundation
DTSTAMP:20260214T003622Z
DTSTART:20260321T120000Z
DESCRIPTION:Want to ride a motorcycle but don’t know where to start? Join C
	ascade Motorcycle Safety and Ride With Us for a chance to experience ridin
	g a motorcycle for free\\\, with professional Cascade Motorcycle Safety Ri
	derCoaches helping you through each step. These 1-on-1\\\, 20-minute sessi
	ons are designed for total beginners\\\, with bikes and helmets provided. 
	\\nThis program is presented with the support of Vulcan Real Estate and Ca
	scade Motorcycle Safety. \\nRide out the remainder of the day in MOHAI to 
	see Kickstands Up! 125 Years of Motorcycling in the PNW. Program participa
	nts will receive a coupon for $5 off museum admission.\n\nFrom MOHAI - Mus
	eum of History & Industry
URL:https://mohai.org/event/motorcycle-riding-experience-with-motorcycle-sa
	fety-foundation/
LOCATION:Block 79 Parking Lot\\\, 711 9th Ave N Seattle WA\\\, 98109\\\, Se
	attle\\\, WA\\\, 98109\\\, United States
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT4H
END:VEVENT
